align=left class=m><span class=title> New Plan: Velk Mondays</span><hr size=1> I love this zone. Biased, sure because it is made for my class--(we're not kos) but still.<br>
<br>
Starting tonight (if I can get enough interest) or next week if I can't, I will be collecting people for groups there. If we get enough people perhaps we can go raid the named ones.<br>
<br>
Now, a few caveats: due to my own limitations, am pretty bad with maps. I know Sobek is the real expert on the zone, and hope to get him to come. I assume others of you know it pretty well as well?<br>
<br>
In any case, in terms of organziing groups, and maintaining order over chaos, I'll do my best to handle that.<br>
<br>
Level range for this...tentatively going to say low forties and up--although I hear the zone has been revamped and is harder now--anyone with knowledge or input on that it would be appreciated. <p><b>Vainne K'harmicdeva
 ~The Nightblind Bard~
<b>~Amnesty, Saryrn~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unayl7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nayl7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/9/01 6:22:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Plan: Velk Mondays</span><hr size=1> My guild has spent a fair amount of time in Velks, originally because it was underused and made great experience hunting in the low to mid forties, and later because of that never ending Coldain Shawl quest (no, really, I like camping spiders for 75 drops!!!).  We have been up and down the ramps in the front from top to bottom.  And we have taken a poke at the Kobolds (and gotten our butts firmly handed to us).  <br>
<br>
What I can tell you about levels is, don't try it with low forties.  The recent change made everything in the front and on the ramps MUCH tougher.  Our experience with it now, in our low fifties, is eerily similar to our initial forays 10 levels ago, except now we know how to navigate the ramps, so we don't just sit at the zone.  Haven't tried the Kobolds again, but, assuming they have not been upgraded, I would suggest two groups of 50ish who know their stuff.  Those dogs hit hard!  <br>
<br>
Finally, another factor to keep in mind about the zone as it now stands.  Since the change, we have found the zone almost constantly crowded with peeps hunting for the new drops, or just hunting spiders for exp. (they are reportedly blue to 60s now).  As we discovered to our dismay, a crowd on those ramps is almost a guarantee of getting trained by someone else's pull.  <br>
<br>
Not meaning to rain on your parade, just a heads up.  <br>
<br>
Nayl Nightglade<br>
52nd Emerald Warrior<br>
Echo of Valor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvainne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vainne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/9/01 11:12:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http--braggarts.shareplay.com-pics-Wythe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Plan: Velk Mondays</span><hr size=1> Yeah so I have been reading. In any case, its Amnesty alt night tonight so tonight won't work.<br>
